  "The steepness of the graph": "",
  "Whether the function has vertical asymptotes": "",
  "Whether the graph curves upward (concave up) or downward (concave down)": "",
  "Concavity describes the direction the graph curves: concave up (bowl-shaped, f'' > 0) or concave down (cap-shaped, f'' < 0). It is determined by the sign of the second derivative.": "",
  "What is 'L'Hopital's Rule' used for?": "",
  "Finding derivatives of composite functions": "",
  "Determining the convergence of series": "",
  "Evaluating limits that result in indeterminate forms like 0/0 or infinity/infinity": "",
  "Integrating rational functions": "",
  "L'Hopital's Rule states that if lim f(x)/g(x) gives 0/0 or infinity/infinity, then lim f(x)/g(x) = lim f'(x)/g'(x), provided the latter limit exists.": "",
  "What is the 'chain rule' in differentiation?": "",
