  "What does the term 'net change' mean in the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus?": "",
  "The total area under the curve, ignoring sign": "",
  "The integral of a rate function f'(x) from a to b equals f(b) - f(a), the total change in f": "",
  "The change in the derivative from a to b": "",
  "The difference between the maximum and minimum of f": "",
  "The Net Change Theorem states that the integral from a to b of f'(x) dx = f(b) - f(a). The integral of a rate of change gives the net change in the original quantity over the interval.": "",
  "What is the 'product rule' for derivatives?": "",
