  "The quotient rule states d/dx[f(x)/g(x)] = [f'(x)g(x) - f(x)g'(x)] / [g(x)]^2. A helpful mnemonic is 'low d-high minus high d-low over low squared.'": "",
  "What is 'related rates' in calculus?": "",
