  "The temperature of a cup of coffee is modeled by T(t) = 70 + 130e^(-0.05t) degrees F, where t is minutes. What is the rate of cooling at t = 10 minutes?": "",
  "Approximately -3.93 degrees F per minute": "",
  "Approximately -1.0 degree F per minute": "",
  "Approximately -6.5 degrees F per minute": "",
  "Approximately -5.0 degrees F per minute": "",
  "T'(t) = 130(-0.05)e^(-0.05t) = -6.5e^(-0.05t). At t = 10: T'(10) = -6.5e^(-0.5) = -6.5(0.6065) = approximately -3.94 degrees F per minute.": "",
  "A ladder 10 feet long leans against a wall. The bottom slides away at 2 ft/s. When the bottom is 6 feet from the wall, how fast is the top sliding down?": "",
  "-3 ft/s": "",
  "-0.75 ft/s": "",
  "-2 ft/s": "",
  "-1.5 ft/s": "",
  "x^2 + y^2 = 100. Differentiating: 2x(dx/dt) + 2y(dy/dt) = 0. When x = 6: y = 8. So 2(6)(2) + 2(8)(dy/dt) = 0, giving dy/dt = -24/16 = -1.5 ft/s.": "",
