  "A company's total cost function is C(x) = x^2 + 100 dollars for x units. What production level minimizes the average cost per unit, C(x)/x?": "",
  "x = 10": "",
  "x = 20": "",
  "x = 50": "",
  "x = 5": "",
  "Average cost AC(x) = C(x)/x = x + 100/x. AC'(x) = 1 - 100/x^2 = 0 gives x^2 = 100, so x = 10 (positive). AC''(10) = 200/1000 > 0 confirms a minimum.": "",
  "Water flows into a tank at rate R(t) = 10 + 3sin(t) gallons per minute and flows out at a constant rate of 8 gallons per minute. At time t = 0, the tank has 50 gallons. How much water is in the tank at t = pi?": "",
  "50 + 2*pi gallons": "",
  "50 gallons": "",
  "50 + 2*pi + 6 gallons": "",
  "56 gallons": "",
  "Net rate = (10 + 3sin t) - 8 = 2 + 3sin t. Amount at t = pi: 50 + integral from 0 to pi of (2 + 3sin t) dt = 50 + [2t - 3cos t] from 0 to pi = 50 + (2pi - 3(-1)) - (0 - 3(1)) = 50 + 2pi + 3 + 3 = 50 + 2pi + 6.": "",
  "If f is continuous on [0, 6] with f(0) = 2 and f(6) = -1, which of the following must be true by the Intermediate Value Theorem?": "",
  "f'(c) = 0 for some c in (0, 6)": "",
  "f is decreasing on (0, 6)": "",
  "f(c) = 0 for some c in (0, 6)": "",
  "f has a maximum at some point in (0, 6)": "",
  "Since f(0) = 2 > 0 and f(6) = -1 < 0, and f is continuous, the IVT guarantees that f(c) = 0 for some c in (0, 6). The function must cross zero at least once.": "",
  "A spherical balloon is inflated at a rate of 10 cubic inches per second. How fast is the radius increasing when the radius is 3 inches?": "",
  "5/(18*pi) inches per second": "",
  "10*pi inches per second": "",
  "10/(12*pi) inches per second": "",
  "10/(36*pi) inches per second": "",
  "V = (4/3)*pi*r^3. dV/dt = 4*pi*r^2 * dr/dt. 10 = 4*pi*(9) * dr/dt. dr/dt = 10/(36*pi) in/s.": "",
  "Let f(x) = integral from 0 to x of (t^2 - 1) dt. On what interval(s) is f decreasing?": "",
  "(-infinity, 0)": "",
  "(-1, 1)": "",
  "(1, infinity)": "",
  "(0, 1)": "",
  "By the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus, f'(x) = x^2 - 1 = (x-1)(x+1). f is decreasing where f'(x) < 0, which is on (-1, 1).": "",
  "A particle has acceleration a(t) = 6t - 2 and initial velocity v(0) = 5. An AP exam question asks: what is the displacement of the particle from t = 0 to t = 3?": "",
  "33": "",
  "18": "",
  "15": "",
  "30": "",
  "v(t) = integral of a(t) dt = 3t^2 - 2t + C. v(0) = 5 gives C = 5, so v(t) = 3t^2 - 2t + 5. Displacement = integral from 0 to 3 of (3t^2 - 2t + 5) dt = [t^3 - t^2 + 5t] from 0 to 3 = 27 - 9 + 15 = 33.": ""
